race.comment: ELLISMAYNE (5) stalked the pace then showed a nice change of gears to arrive late and collect his maiden win over this distance at Nowra last start. Progressing in good fashion and with 2kgs less out of the inside draw is going to play a major role again. IRISH JIG (6) is back after a five-month spell. Tried over longer trips at the start of last prep without success. Hit form when he dropped back to 1280m later in the campaign. Goes fast and will give them something to catch. FAMOSO (1) has worked through the line well in his two runs this time in work, both over 1100m. Wears winkers for the first time and gets out to a more suitable trip so this looks a very winnable race. LONGINUS (3) returns from an eight-month spell. Best figure last prep was achieved first-up. Trialled well recently and should be ready to run a bold race. MEET ME IN BONDI (2) scored first-up over this distance at Wyong last campaign so he is one to consider coming off a 29-week spell.
